- [ ] 500g 5% Fat Minced Beef
- [ ] 300g Ditalini Pasta
- [ ] 1 Diced Red Onion
- [ ] 3 Crushed Garlic Cloves
- [ ] 1 Tsp Smoked Paprika 
- [ ] 1 Tsp Mustard Powder 
- [ ] 1 Tsp Worcestershire Sauce 
- [ ] A Pinch Of Black Pepper 
- [ ] 1 Tbsp Tomato Purée 
- [ ] 15 Chopped (Half) Tomatoes 
- [ ] ¼ Tin Chopped Tomatoes 
- [ ] 3 Slices American Burger Cheese 
- [ ] 80g Grated Mature Cheddar 

1. Fry off your red onion. After a few mins add your Garlic and fry for another 30 seconds.

2. The add in your beef mince and break it up, once the beef has some colour in it add in your Paprika, Mustard Powder, Worcestershire Sauce, Black Pepper then add in your Tomato Purée.

3. Now add in your tomatoes and mix for a minute or so, now tip in your ¼ tin of Chopped Tomatoes. Mix for another minutes before adding the American Cheese, give it a good mix and add a cup of your Pasta water mix again.

4. Finally pour in your cooked and strained Pasta, stir though then scatter Grated Cheddar on top. 
